      "version": 75,
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "id": "fvag9RzO8rL-rKPUxpuGL",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 9744.43661267644,
      "y": -510.81604589561675,
      "width": 368,
      "height": 274,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "seed": 759007600,
      "versionNonce": 1095870832,
      "text": "Existing PostIdentityCreation webhook is\nextended to also process invitations:\n  1.  read invitation_ref from Ory payload\n  2.  validate hash · expiry · email match\n  3.  create TenantMember\n  4.  mark invitation Accepted\n  5.  emit Permit.io sync\n\nNew tiny redirector endpoint:\n  GET  /invitations/finalize?invitation=…\n    →  302  {HubBaseUrl}/{tenantSlug}\n\nFor existing-account flows (State 1 & 2), the same\nlogic wires into Ory's after_login hook.\n\nTenantInvitation gains the same token fields\nas in C/D — but the token rides as part of\nOry's flow metadata, not in a custom URL.",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 10,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Existing PostIdentityCreation webhook is\nextended to also process invitations:\n  1.  read invitation_ref from Ory payload\n  2.  validate hash · expiry · email match\n  3.  create TenantMember\n  4.  mark invitation Accepted\n  5.  emit Permit.io sync\n\nNew tiny redirector endpoint:\n  GET  /invitations/finalize?invitation=…\n    →  302  {HubBaseUrl}/{tenantSlug}\n\nFor existing-account flows (State 1 & 2), the same\nlogic wires into Ory's after_login hook.\n\nTenantInvitation gains the same token fields\nas in C/D — but the token rides as part of\nOry's flow metadata, not in a custom URL.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "index": "bT9",
      "autoResize": true
    },
