      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "seed": 1052757904,
      "versionNonce": 1985705872,
      "text": "Link IS the entire authentication step:\n\n  {AccountServiceUrl}/invite/magic\n    ?token=…\n\nToken is:\n  •  cryptographically random (256-bit)\n  •  sha-256 hashed at rest\n  •  single-use\n  •  short-lived (e.g. 24h, not 7d)\n  •  bound to invitation.Email\n\nPossession of the link == authentication.\nThis is the controversial bit — the token\nstops being 'just an invitation identifier'\nand becomes an auth credential.",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 10,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Link IS the entire authentication step:\n\n  {AccountServiceUrl}/invite/magic\n    ?token=…\n\nToken is:\n  •  cryptographically random (256-bit)\n  •  sha-256 hashed at rest\n  •  single-use\n  •  short-lived (e.g. 24h, not 7d)\n  •  bound to invitation.Email\n\nPossession of the link == authentication.\nThis is the controversial bit — the token\nstops being 'just an invitation identifier'\nand becomes an auth credential.",
